# C++ headers

- **Few exported names** — entry + shared state/data only.
- **No one-liner wrappers** — inline; don’t add a name without real logic.
- **Struct when shared** — pass snapshot `const&` between sites; no return bags.
- **One read pass** — load shared state once, pass downstream.
- **Concrete over generic** — unroll fixed sequences; abstract when N or direction varies.
- **Split files** only when a second real caller exists — not for planned work.

Before adding a name: used in >1 place or stable API? non-trivial? can’t stay readable inlined? Any **no** → don’t add it.

# Comments

- Short; on new/changed code.
- **Why** or non-obvious invariant — not what the line does.
- Prefer one line.

```cpp
// BAD: increment counter
++n;

// GOOD: single-writer gate — one eval per burst
if (gate.exchange(1) != 0) return;
```
